<plot>In some Native traditions there is a story about a Tribal Chief who is walking along with his young son one day. The Chief turns to his son and says, 'within each and every one of us, in every human heart there exists two wolves, one of love and one of hate.' The boy thinks for a moment before speaking and asks, 'well, which of these two wolves is the strongest'? To which the Chief replies, 'the one which is fed'. 'Duality' kindles this spiritual tenet through the story of loving husband and father Chris Watson who straddles the thin line between reality and fantasy in a dark examination of the human psyche. Chris's intense world becomes thoughtful food for our reflection.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?161261</url></doc>
